  "text": "0 CS : a set of candidate hypotheses 0 SS : a set of selected hypotheses The algorithm comes up with a set of fuzzy hypotheses supported more strongly than the support degree threshold value r. In line 5, the support degree of each hypothesis is computed. Among them, only hypotheses supported more strongly than the given threshold value T , are refined in line [CITATION_1] . In virtue of this threshold value, some noisy data due to either wrong inputs or genuine exceptions can not affect the major results. In Section 4.2, an example showing how the algorithm operates is provided.",
